  Act

 means Public Act No. 10, 73d Congress, as amended and as reenacted
and amended by the Agricultural Marketing Agreement Act of 1937, as
amended (

  48 Stat. 31

, as amended; 


    7 U.S.C. 601


 et seq.; 

  68 Stat. 906, 1047

).

P.text:
 Three producer members, including at least one who predominately
produces seed potatoes, and one handler member, with their
respective alternates, from District No. 1;

 To appoint such employees, agents, and representatives as it may
deem necessary and to determine the salaries and define the duties
of each such person;

 At the beginning of each fiscal period to submit to the Secretary a
budget of its expenses for such fiscal period, together with a
report thereon;

 Certify to the committee and to the Secretary that potatoes
received from the production area for processing will be used for
such purposes and will not be placed in fresh market channels;
